<!-- ===================================================
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
==================================================== -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">A major outer southern hub with amenity, access and a broad buyer pool.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Springwood is one of Brisbane's larger outer southern suburbs, sitting approximately 25 kilometres from the CBD at the junction of the Pacific Motorway corridor and the Logan Motorway network. It functions as a genuine hub for the outer southern catchment: the suburb's retail precinct, together with the nearby Logan Hyperdome at Shailer Park, services a wide residential population. This hub character creates a different buyer dynamic than the pure family estate suburbs in the corridor, with a broader buyer pool that includes first home buyers, investors, families and downsizers all active in the market.
    </p>
<!-- APPRAISAL FORM -->
<div style="background:#fff; border-left:4px solid #b98229; padding:2rem 2rem 1.75rem; margin:2rem 0; border-radius:16px;">
