<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Understanding which buyer segment is most relevant to your specific property is the starting point for any well-run campaign in Springwood. The suburb's housing stock is genuinely varied: established post-war homes on larger blocks in the older residential streets, 1990s brick estate homes in the newer pockets, and some townhouse and unit stock near the retail and commercial areas. Each type attracts a different buyer, and the pricing, marketing and timing strategy that works for a four-bedroom estate home will not work for an older post-war home with subdivision potential.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The Pacific Motorway gives Springwood commuters direct access to the Brisbane CBD in approximately 30 to 35 minutes, and to the Gold Coast in a comparable time in the other direction. Logan Hospital, approximately 10 minutes away via the motorway, is a significant employment destination for residents in the southern corridor. The combination of motorway access, major retail, hospital proximity and diverse housing stock means Springwood draws buyers from a wider geographic area than many of its southern corridor neighbours.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
