    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about Springwood.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Springwood?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Springwood's value is driven by its status as a major outer southern hub with exceptional retail and service amenity, strong Pacific Motorway access, and a genuinely diverse housing stock that attracts a broad buyer pool. School catchments, particularly Springwood State High School and the surrounding primary schools, are actively researched by families. Its hub status and access to Logan Hospital create investor demand that sits alongside owner-occupier buyers throughout the year.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Springwood?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-presented Springwood homes typically sell within 28 to 45 days when correctly priced. The suburb's diverse buyer pool means that a well-positioned campaign will find inquiry from multiple buyer segments simultaneously. Properties near the Springwood retail precinct with good access and strong presentation are among the fastest-moving in the suburb.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Springwood?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Springwood is one of the outer southern corridor's best-serviced suburbs for everyday life: major retail, good school options, Logan Hospital proximity, and direct Pacific Motorway access to the CBD and Gold Coast. The suburb mixes established residential streets with newer estate pockets, creating a varied streetscape. Residents value the self-contained nature of the suburb and the commute options it affords.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Springwood a good suburb to buy in right now?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Springwood offers genuine value for buyers who want outer-southern Brisbane convenience and amenity at accessible price points. Its diverse housing stock gives buyers options across a range of budgets, and the suburb's hub status with major retail and good transport means that lifestyle credentials remain strong relative to price. Investor demand alongside owner-occupier buyers creates competition across more property types than in purely residential estate suburbs.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

